==English==

{{rank|once|new|years|169|always|another|right|each}}

===Etymology===
From '''all''' + '''way'''. The '''s''' is an adverbial ending, originally a genitive ending.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ɔlˈwez/
*{{audio|en-us-always.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adverb===
'''always'''

# At all times; ever; perpetually; throughout all time; continually:
#: ''God is always the same.''
#: ''Even in Heaven his [Mammon's] looks and thoughts.'' --Milton.
# Constancy during a certain period, or regularly at stated intervals; invariably; uniformly;&mdash;opposed to {sometimes} or {occasionally}.
#: ''He always rides a black galloway.'' --Bulwer.
<!-- material copied from Webster's Revised Unabridged Dictionary (1913) -->

